President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to appoint Richard Grenell to a key position in his Administration. Grenell will serve concurrently as the Special Presidential Envoy for Serbia and Kosovo Peace Negotiations and as the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Federal Republic of Germany. Grenell has been serving as the United States Ambassador to Germany since May 8, 2018. He is a foreign policy writer and commentator who founded the international consulting firm Capitol Media Partners in 2010. Grenell has also worked as a primary communications adviser for public officials at various levels of government and for a Fortune 200 ranked company. He has extensive experience as the longest-serving United States spokesman at the United Nations, having served four United States Ambassadors. Grenell holds a B.A. from Evangel University and an MPA from Harvard University's John F. Kennedy School of Government.